example:
Non-functional requirement and matching test plan:

Requirement NFR-PERF-01:
'Under a sustained load of 1000 concurrent users for 10 minutes, the /search endpoint must keep p95 response time below 2000ms and error rate below 1%.'

k6 load test script:
```javascript
import http from 'k6/http';
import { check, sleep } from 'k6';

export const options = {
  stages: [
    { duration: '2m', target: 1000 }, // ramp up to 1000 users
    { duration: '10m', target: 1000 }, // hold peak load
    { duration: '2m', target: 0 },    // ramp down
  ],
  thresholds: {
    http_req_duration: ['p(95)<2000'], // p95 under 2s
    http_req_failed: ['rate<0.01'],    // <1% errors
  },
};

export default function () {
  const res = http.get('https://shop.example.com/search?q=shoes');
  check(res, { 'status is 200': (r) => r.status === 200 });
  sleep(1);
}
```
If either threshold fails, k6 exits non-zero and the NFR is breached.
